description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*** IMMEDIATE START ***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;30hrs per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has risen within our Reception team at Dr Samuel and Dr Khan practice based at Vicarage Lane Health Centre (Stratford, East London)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for flexible, hardworking and friendly person to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be required to work&lt;strong&gt;30hrs p/w, shifts of 5 - 6 hrs between 8am and 8pm Monday to Friday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To manage the flow of patients arriving at the reception desk, for appointments or queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To coordinate patient journey using EMIS Web and ERS systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make appointments over the telephone, at the reception desk and on the computer system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately and timely processing of booking forms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To undertake the registration of patients and deal appropriately with the inputting of all their details using the computer system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To deal with the incoming and outgoing mail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To deal with prescriptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required experience and skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To have administrative experience in a healthcare environment (preferably within the GP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ability to manage fast pace and a very busy environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remain calm under pressure and when dealing with challenging situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of medical terminology, knowledge of reproductive medicine is an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General computer skills (Microsoft Windows and Office Suite, EMIS is an advantage )&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation and phone manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good general professionalism, including confidentiality and work ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A warm and welcoming manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to be dynamic and sympathetic (we deal with patients in difficult situations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well organised and systematic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meticulous attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a prestigious professional environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage workload, prioritise, follow-up and ensure all tasks are performed in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;30hrs p/w, shifts ranging from 8am to 8pm Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 Days Holiday per Annum, plus paid UK Public Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to grow within an organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working along very friendly and supportive team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;Part Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Receptionist: 1 year (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;London, East London (Required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Type: Part-time&lt;/p&gt;
